ircd-phatbox installation instructions

#1 QUICK START

  1. Configure:

    ./configure --prefix=/home/user/ircd

  2. Build:

    make

  3. Install:

    make install

#2 CONFIGURE OPTIONS

  --prefix=/path/to/install
      Required. Do not run the IRCd as root. The IRCd user needs write
      access to its own directories.

  --enable-openssl
      Enable OpenSSL for CHALLENGE and encrypted links. Usually
      auto-detected. If not found automatically:
        --enable-openssl=/path/to/openssl

      To generate a self-signed certificate after install:
        /path/to/ircd/bin/genssl.sh

  --enable-static
      Build a static-linked IRCd. Modules cannot be loaded/unloaded
      at runtime.

  --enable-assert
      Enable debugging assertions. Do not use on production servers.

  --enable-services
      Enable services daemon compatibility. See doc/services.txt.

  --enable-ocf-services
      Enable OpenChanfix hooks.

  --enable-jemalloc / --enable-tcmalloc / --enable-tcmalloc-minimal
      Use an alternate memory allocator.

#3 UPGRADING

  If upgrading from ircd-ratbox 2.x or ircd-hybrid 7.x, you will need
  to import your old ban files. See bin/bantool for details:

    bantool -i -d /path/to/old/etc

  If upgrading from ircd-ratbox 3.x, run bantool -u after every upgrade
  to update the database schema.

#4 BUG REPORTS

  Report bugs at: https://github.com/dcorbe/ircd-phatbox/issues

  If ircd-phatbox crashes, include a gdb backtrace:

    gdb bin/ircd-phatbox ircd.core
    (gdb) bt

  Keep the binary, modules, and core file in case developers need them.
  Do not use 'make install-strip' if you plan to submit bug reports.
